duck: Goal seeking - In computing, goal seeking is the ability to calculate backward to obtain an input that would result in a given output.
Disk seek, in which the read head of a magnetic disk repositions itself
Rent seeking - In economics, rent-seeking is an attempt to derive economic rent by manipulating the social or political environment in which economic activities occur, rather than by adding value.
Zero seek - Zero seek is a mechanical engineering design component of most computer-controlled data storage devices, including floppy disk drives, tape drives, and early hard drives.
Job seeking - Job hunting, job seeking, or job searching is the act of looking for employment, due to unemployment or discontent with a current position.
